author: MANUEL MORENO JR.
title: Clear Creek clinches share of district tennis crown, Texas City forced to wait
text: Texas City moves forward on new subdivision Developers for a 300-lot housing development in east Texas City cleared another hurdle Wednesday. City commissioners approved a development agreement with Galveston Bay Investors, LLC, a League City-based development company, allowing its 85 acres west of Pelican Harbour Drive to be annexed into a municipal utility district in exchange for certain housing requirements and obligations. Retired firefighter gets teaching job If it has a motor, students in Dickinson High School’s advanced automotive class can fix it. So, when a 1942 fire truck, donated to the Dickinson Volunteer Fire Department in September, was brought in to the school’s automotive shop with the goal to get it back up and running, Brad Vandenhul and his class eagerly took on the challenge.
